Former Senator and 2023 Kaduna Gubernatorial aspirant, Shehu Sani, has reacted to reports of Dornier Airlines resuming a twice-weekly Abuja-Kaduna route. According to the former lawmaker via his official Twitter page on Monday, Dornier Airlines should drop the passengers at the Old Airport inside the city, not at the outskirts. He wrote, “Dornier Airlines’ decision to start a twice-weekly Abuja-Kaduna route is a welcome development. -Advertisement- “But pls drop the passengers at the Old Airport inside the city and not the new Airport at the outskirts.”